==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Liquate
<hw>Li"quate</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧"kw⟦amac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>liquatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>liquare</ets> to
melt.]</ety> <def>To melt; to become liquid.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Woodward.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Liquate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Liquate
<hw>Li"quate</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <fld>(Metal.)</fld> <def>To separate
by fusion, as a more fusible from a less fusible material.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Liquation</ent>⟦br⟧
